Types of Hackers

Here's a debriefing on types of hackers

Black Hat The stereotypical ‘hacker’ – the kind you hear about on the news.


White Hat The Yang to the Black Hat’s Yin, White Hat hackers are the polar opposite of the Black Hat in every way.


Grey Hat Nothing in life is black and white, and neither is hacking.


Blue Hat Vengeful and aggressive in every way- but only if you create them.


Red Hat The caped crusaders of the cyber world.


Baby hackers taking their first steps in the cyber world. Motives: Learning to be full blown hackers.


Script Kiddie This is something of an ‘odd one out’, since it’s neither a hat or a colour! But a Script Kiddie can still cause problems, no matter how innocent the name sounds.
